      <api:name>g_menu_item_set_icon</api:name>
      <api:arg>
        <api:type>Gio.Icon</api:type>
        <api:name>icon</api:name>
      </api:arg>
    </api:function>
  </info>
  <title>Gio.MenuItem.prototype.set_icon</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_icon(icon: Gio.Icon): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_menu_item_set_icon()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets (or unsets) the icon on <code>menu_item</code>.</p>  <p>This call is the same as calling <link xref="Gio.Icon.serialize"/> and using the
result as the value to <link xref="Gio.MenuItem.set_attribute_value"/> for
%G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_ICON.</p>  <p>This API is only intended for use with "noun" menu items; things like
bookmarks or applications in an "Open With" menu.  Don't use it on
menu items corresponding to verbs (eg: stock icons for 'Save' or
'Quit').</p>  <p>If <code>icon</code> is <code>null</code> then the icon is unset.</p>
  <p>Since 2.38</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>icon</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.Icon"/>, or <code>null</code></p>
</item>
